# ðŸ§¹ Hard Drive Cleanup (Directory Size Analyzer)

A simple **command-line Node.js application** written in **TypeScript** that recursively scans a starting directory and reports the sizes of all files and directories.  
Useful for analyzing how disk space is being used in a folder tree.

---

## ðŸ“¦ Features

- Recursively scans directories starting from a given folder  
- Displays file paths, types (file/directory), and human-readable sizes  
- Outputs a JSON-style array of all directories and files  
- Includes a help flag (`-h` or `--help`) to display usage information  
- Written in **TypeScript** and runs on **Node.js**

---

## ðŸ§° Requirements

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (v18+ recommended)
- [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/)
- NPM package: [`filesize`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/filesize)